      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Relative hemolysis index (RH) validation against in-vitro blood damage measurements",
      "description": "Predicted RH values computed via power-law hemolysis model (Giersiepen et al.) integrated over Lagrangian particle tracks. Compared against in-vitro RH measurements at five flow-speed operating points on the FDA generic centrifugal pump. All five predicted RH values fall below the RH < 1 acceptance threshold; mean prediction error 9.7% relative to measured values. Mesh independence confirmed on three grids (3.2M, 8.1M, 16.4M cells).",
      "description2": "NOTE: Uncertainty quantification for this validation result was deferred pending availability of additional experimental replicates. The team judged the single-replicate experimental dataset sufficient for MRL 2 decision support without formal UQ propagation."
    },
